                <h1>Can Employers Access Juvenile Records? Understanding Your Rights</h1>
                <p>Employers generally cannot access juvenile records due to privacy laws protecting minors. These records are sealed to encourage rehabilitation without the stigma of a criminal past. However, specific circumstances or certain types of employment may allow for exceptions. Always check local laws for clarity on this matter.</p>
